text: Hamperokken () is a mountain in Tromsø Municipality in Troms og Finnmark county, Norway. At tall, it is the highest mountain peak on the mainland peninsula west of the Ullsfjorden. Hamperokken has the 6th most prominent peak in Norway with a prominence of . The mountain sits about west of the village of Fagernes and the European route E8 and it is also about southeast of the city of Tromsø. ==References== Category:Mountains of Troms og Finnmark Category:Tromsø
